Petkim Petrokimya Holding AS (PETKM) ,  Turkey â€™s
biggest chemicals maker, fell after reporting a first-quarter
loss of 7.9 million liras ($4.5 million), missing estimates.  The shares retreated 1.4 percent to 2.06 liras at the close
in Istanbul, slipping a second day to the lowest since Jan. 31.  The company was expected to earn 10.3 million liras,
according to the average of seven analyst estimates compiled by
Bloomberg. Petkim reported net income of 77.2 million liras in
the first quarter last year.  To contact the reporter on this story:
